'''Pamela Gail Fryman''' (born August 19, 1959) is an [[United States|American]] [[sitcom]] [[television director|director]] and [[Television producer|producer]]. She directed all but twelve episodes of the television series ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]''.

==Early life==
Fryman was born and grew up in [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]].<ref name="dga">{{cite web|title=DGA Quarterly Spring 2010 - Director Profile: Pamela Fryman|url=http://www.dgaquarterly.org/BACKISSUES/Spring2010/DirectorProfilePamelaFryman.aspx|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20110228160011/http://www.dgaquarterly.org/BACKISSUES/Spring2010/DirectorProfilePamelaFryman.aspx|archivedate=2011-02-28|df=}}</ref>

==Career==
Fryman got her first job on ''The John Davidson Show'' as an assistant to the talent coordinator, and went on to be a booth production assistant and secretary on ''[[Santa Barbara (TV series)|Santa Barbara]]'', eventually moving up to assistant director (AD), and director.<ref name="dga" /> In 1993, producer [[Peter Noah]], with whom she had worked on the game show ''[[Dream House (game show)|Dream House]]'', gave Fryman a chance to direct an episode of the short-lived sitcom ''[[Café Americain]]''. These would be the first stepping stones toward a long and successful career.<ref name="dga"/>

Before her directing career blossomed, Fryman pursued stage directing. On the set of ''[[Frasier]]'', rehearsal resembled a play staging, which is exactly what creator and executive producer [[David Lee (screenwriter)|David Lee]] had in mind when he hired her.<ref name="DGA - January 1999">{{cite web|title=DGA Magazine January 1999 - Fraiser|url=http://stage.dga.org/news/mag_archives/v23-5/v23-5.htm}}</ref> Fryman directed 34 episodes of the show from seasons four through eight.

Fryman directed the majority of the episodes of ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]''.<ref>{{cite news 
| title = Neil Patrick Harris Directs Episode of 'How I Met Your Mother' Airing 1/18
| url = http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Neil_Patrick_Harris_Directs_Episode_of_How_I_Met_Your_Mother_Airing_118_20100118 
| work = BroadwayWorld.com 
| quote = Though a series regular, this will mark Harris's directing debut, and a rarity for the show as Pamela Fryman has directed 92 of 'How I Met Your Mother's' 97 episodes. 
| accessdate = 2010-01-30 
}} 
</ref> Show creator [[Craig Thomas (screenwriter)|Craig Thomas]] praised her communication skills, saying, "She makes everyone feel they've been heard and respected and she can connect with anyone."<ref name="latimes">{{cite news 
| date = October 19, 2008 
| author = Maria Elena Fernandez 
| title =  The set mom on 'How I Met Your Mother'
| url = http://articles.latimes.com/2008/oct/19/entertainment/ca-mother19 
| newspaper = [[Los Angeles Times]] 
| pages = 3
}} 
</ref>
Though Fryman's original career plan did not include directing (she figured she would "follow in her father's footsteps in merchandising"),<ref name="dga"/> she has grown to realize that directing is her forte and passion. In [[Variety (magazine)|''Variety'']] magazine, Fryman said that continuing to direct ''How I Met Your Mother'' is her fantasy realized.<ref>{{cite news 
| title = Dreams from the top
| url =  http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118038332/
| work = variety.com
| quote = continuing to direct "How I Met Your Mother" is her fantasy realized." 
| accessdate = 2012-05-06 
}} 
</ref> In 2014, she officiated the wedding of ''How I Met Your Mother'' co-star [[Neil Patrick Harris]] and [[David Burtka]], who played a side role in the show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/article/neil-patrick-harris-marries-david-burtka/|title=Neil Patrick Harris Marries David Burtka|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-03-03|language=en}}</ref>

== Awards ==
Fryman has received recognition from the [[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] also known as the (ATAS), the [[National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences]], the [[Directors Guild of America]], Goldderby.com, the Online Film & Television Association also known as the (OFTA), and the [[Women in Film Crystal + Lucy Awards|Women in Film]] organization.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0296945/awards|title=Pamela Fryman|website=IMDb|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref>

* 1990 '''WON''' - [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series Directing Team|'''Daytime Emmy award for Outstanding Drama Series Directing Team''']] (''[[Santa Barbara (TV series)|Santa Barbara]]'')
* 1991 '''WON''' - [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series Directing Team|'''Daytime Emmy award for Outstanding Drama Series Directing Team''']] (''Santa Barbara'')
* 1998 Nominated - [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing – Comedy Series|Directors Guild award for Outstanding Directorial Achievement in Comedy Series]] ("[[List of Frasier episodes|Halloween (Part 1)]]") (''[[Frasier]]'')
* 1999 Nominated - [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing – Comedy Series|Directors Guild award for Outstanding Directorial Achievement in Comedy Series]] ("[[List of Just Shoot Me! episodes|Two Girls for Every Boy]]") (''[[Just Shoot Me!]]'')
* 2000 Nominated - [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing – Comedy Series|Directors Guild award for Outstanding Directorial Achievement in Comedy Series]] ("[[List of Frasier episodes|The Flight Before Christmas]]") (''Frasier'')
* 2001 Nominated - [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing – Comedy Series|Directors Guild award for Outstanding Directorial Achievement in Comedy Series]] ("[[List of Frasier episodes|And The Dish Ran Away With The Spoon (Part 1 & 2)]]") (''Frasier'')
* 2007 Nominated - [[Gold Derby Awards|Gold Derby award for Comedy Episode of the Year]] ("[[List of How I Met Your Mother episodes|Slap Bet]]") (''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'')
* 2009 Nominated - [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Comedy Series|Primetime Emmy award for Outstanding Comedy Series]] (''How I Met Your Mother'')
* 2011 Nominated - Online Film & Television Association award for Best Direction in a Comedy Series (''How I Met Your Mother'')
* 2011 Nominated - [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Comedy Series|Primetime Emmy award for Outstanding Directing for a Comedy Series]] ("[[List of How I Met Your Mother episodes|Subway Wars]]") (''How I Met Your Mother'')
* 2011 '''WON''' - [[Women in Film Crystal + Lucy Awards|'''Women in Film Crystal + Lucy award, Dorothy Arzner Directors award''']]
* 2014 Nominated - [[Gold Derby Awards|Gold Derby award for Comedy Episode of the Year]] ("[[List of How I Met Your Mother episodes|How Your Mother Met Me]]") (''How I Met Your Mother'')

